  - central-binomial-sums
  - Mahler-measure
  - Dirichlet-L-functions
abstract: >-
  A discovery framework for closed-form mathematical identities. Evaluates
  parameterized series families (central-binomial, Dirichlet character,
  harmonic-weighted, BBP-style multirational, Ramanujan-Sato factorial,
  Mahler measure, etc.) at high precision and runs PSLQ to find short
  integer relations against a basis of standard mathematical constants.
  Sixteen known identities are blind-rediscovered as pytest fixtures,
  including Apery 1978, Bailey-Borwein-Plouffe 1995, Euler 1775, and the
  classical Catalan formula. Built in approximately one evening with
  Anthropic's Claude as collaborator; intended primarily as a teaching
  artifact and reproducible search tool.
